Cook the noodles as per instructions on the pack and drain. Rinse in cold water, drain thoroughly and toss in sesame oil to keep the noodles separate.Heat a little groundnut oil in a hot wok. Add the ginger and  garlic and stir fry briefly. Add the mushrooms and mangetout. Stir fry for 2-3 minutes over a high heat.Add the noodles, the soy sauce, sherry, seasoning and sugar and stir fry briefly before adding the salad onions, pak choi and beansprouts.Drizzle with sesame oil just before serving.